#### **3.3.7** Redundant Entry

Level A(Added in 2.2)

Information previously entered by or provided to the user that is required to be entered again in the same process is either: Show Hide full description

* * *

*   auto-populated, or
    
*   available for the user to select.
    

Except when:

* * *

*   re-entering the information is essential,
    
*   the information is required to ensure the security of the content, or
    
*   previously entered information is no longer valid.
    

[Understanding 3.3.7](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/redundant-entry.html)

Show Hide techniques and failures for 3.3.7

##### Sufficient Techniques for Success Criterion 3.3.7

Note: Other techniques may also be sufficient if they meet the success criterion. See [Understanding Techniques.](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/understanding-techniques)

*   [G221: Provide data from a previous step in a process](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Techniques/general/G221)
*   Not requesting the same information twice (Potential future technique)

[SHARE](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/quickref/?currentsidebar=%23col_customize&showtechniques=312&levels=aaa#redundant-entry)

Link to this section: Shortcut to copy the link: ctrl+C _or_ ⌘C

